title: Barry Lyndon
overview: An Irish rogue wins the heart of a rich widow and assumes her dead husband's aristocratic position in 18th-century England.

title: The Great Escape
overview: Allied prisoners of war plan for several hundred of their number to escape from a German camp during World War II.

title: Ben-Hur
overview: After a Jewish prince is betrayed and sent into slavery by a Roman friend, he regains his freedom and comes back for revenge.

title: Fitzcarraldo
overview: The story of Brian Sweeney Fitzgerald, an extremely determined man who intends to build an opera house in the middle of a jungle.

title: Spartacus
overview: The slave Spartacus leads a violent revolt against the decadent Roman Republic.

title: Deliverance
overview: Intent on seeing the Cahulawassee River before it's dammed and turned into a lake, outdoor fanatic Lewis Medlock takes his friends on a canoeing trip they'll never forget into the dangerous American back-country.

title: Interstate 60: Episodes of the Road
overview: Neal Oliver, a very confused young man and an artist, takes a journey of a lifetime on a highway I60 that doesn't exist on any of the maps, going to the places he never even heard of, searching for an answer and his dreamgirl.

title: Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows: Part 2
overview: Harry, Ron, and Hermione search for Voldemort's remaining Horcruxes in their effort to destroy the Dark Lord as the final battle rages on at Hogwarts.

title: Stagecoach
overview: A group of people traveling on a stagecoach find their journey complicated by the threat of Geronimo and learn something about each other in the process.

title: Nebraska
overview: An aging, booze-addled father makes the trip from Montana to Nebraska with his estranged son in order to claim a million-dollar Mega Sweepstakes Marketing prize.

title: 12 Years a Slave
overview: In the antebellum United States, Solomon Northup, a free black man from upstate New York, is abducted and sold into slavery.

title: Lagaan: Once Upon a Time in India
overview: The people of a small village in Victorian India stake their future on a game of cricket against their ruthless British rulers.

title: Dead Man
overview: On the run after murdering a man, accountant William Blake encounters a strange aboriginal American man named Nobody who prepares him for his journey into the spiritual world.

title: Hamilton
overview: The real life of one of America's foremost founding fathers and first Secretary of the Treasury, Alexander Hamilton. Captured live on Broadway from the Richard Rodgers Theater with the original Broadway cast.
stars: ['Lin-Manuel Miranda', 'Phillipa Soo', 'Leslie Odom Jr.', 'Renée Elise Goldsberry']

title: Straight Outta Compton
overview: The rap group NWA emerges from the mean streets of Compton in Los Angeles, California, in the mid-1980s and revolutionizes Hip Hop culture with their music and tales about life in the hood.
stars: ["O'Shea Jackson Jr.", 'Corey Hawkins', 'Jason Mitchell', 'Neil Brown Jr.']

title: Hacksaw Ridge
overview: World War II American Army Medic Desmond T. Doss, who served during the Battle of Okinawa, refuses to kill people, and becomes the first man in American history to receive the Medal of Honor without firing a shot.

title: Interstellar
overview: A team of explorers travel through a wormhole in space in an attempt to ensure humanity's survival.

title: Mississippi Burning
overview: Two F.B.I. Agents with wildly different styles arrive in Mississippi to investigate the disappearance of some civil rights activists.

title: Amadeus
overview: The life, success and troubles of Wolfgang Amadeus Mozart, as told by Antonio Salieri, the contemporaneous composer who was insanely jealous of Mozart's talent and claimed to have murdered him.

title: Queen
overview: A Delhi girl from a traditional family sets out on a solo honeymoon after her marriage gets cancelled.
